{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d916a610-2fd1-4b37-864c-5e52faf13a76","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changed\n\nThe old VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) doesn't work with MTP. Use `--filter` with the new **treenode filter** syntax instead:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests AND Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **`&`** → **`AND`** (logical operators are words: `AND`, `OR`, `NOT`)\n- `~` (contains), `=`, `!=` operators still work\n\n### 2. No code changes needed\n\nYour `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attribute works the same in xUnit v3, so `IntegrationTests.cs` stays as-is.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Old (VSTest / xUnit v2) | New (MTP / xUnit v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"` | `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests AND Category=Smoke\"` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3bc1fdd7-6c9f-45ce-96d2-f9112e98ad5a","outputTokens":280,"requestId":"1BD1:C7BCA:223005A:259B444:6A03CFDB"},"id":"f2dd9684-5b64-4d19-a565-09d17a227857","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:12:02.545Z","parentId":"a3004bb5-ceb1-4d58-aa45-c5ff9468d597"}
